From df128b7b0dce038716aef67d826d5fb6870fcaaa Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Christian Walter <christian.walter@9elements.com>
Date: Sun, 1 Mar 2026 00:16:19 +0100
Subject: [PATCH] smbios-mdr: Add PCIeDevice D-Bus objects from SMBIOS Type 9
Upstream-Status: Submitted [https://gerrit.openbmc.org/c/openbmc/smbios-mdr/+/87924]

SMBIOS Type 9 (System Slots) records are already parsed to create
PCIeSlot D-Bus objects. However, bmcweb's PCIeDevice Redfish handler
queries for xyz.openbmc_project.Inventory.Item.PCIeDevice objects
which currently are not created, leaving the Redfish PCIeDevices
collection empty.

Add a PcieDevice class that creates a PCIeDevice D-Bus object for
each SMBIOS Type 9 slot, alongside the existing PCIeSlot object.
Each PCIeDevice exposes GenerationInUse, GenerationSupported, and
MaxLanes derived from the same Type 9 data, and creates a
contained_by association to its corresponding PCIeSlot object
so bmcweb can populate the Slot sub-object in the Redfish response.

Introduced pcie-device-dbus meson option which by default, will
be disabled. When enabled, PCIeDevice objects are exposed on D-Bus.

Tested:
1) PCIeDevice objects appear on D-Bus after SMBIOS data is loaded
2) D-Bus properties are populated correctly
3) Individual PCIeDevice response includes Slot sub-object

Change-Id: I43394340b019745bd2fef32a30eb2ebbc28ff2bc
Signed-off-by: Christian Walter <christian.walter@9elements.com>
